This paper involves natural language communication and visual grounding, which are commonly studied in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses computer vision techniques to identify visual objects in a complex scene, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes an interactive training method that involves reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.RO.
